# Apple Pay Domain Verification File
# 
# IMPORTANT: This is a placeholder file for the POC.
# 
# To set up Apple Pay domain verification:
# 
# 1. Log in to your Apple Developer account
# 2. Go to Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles
# 3. Select your Merchant ID
# 4. Click "Configure" next to Apple Pay
# 5. Add your domain (e.g., yourdomain.com)
# 6. Download the domain association file
# 7. Replace this file with the downloaded content
# 8. Ensure the file is accessible at:
#    https://yourdomain.com/.well-known/apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association
#
# For local development, you may need to:
# - Use ngrok or similar to create a public HTTPS URL
# - Configure your domain in Apple Developer portal
# - Test with Apple Pay in Safari on a real device
#
# The actual file should contain JSON with your merchant ID and domain verification data.
